&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OXFORD UNIVERSITY HOSPITALS Foundation NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT IN PAEDIATRIC ANAESTHESIA WITH AN INTEREST IN PAEDIATRIC ACUTE AND CHRONIC PAIN MANAGEMENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to apply for the above post for the Department of Anaesthetics at the John Radcliffe Hospital, Headley Way, Headington, Oxford OX3 9DU.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting new post to join the Paediatric Anaesthetic Group at the Oxford University Hospitals Foundation NHS Trust for a candidate with an interest in acute and chronic pain management. The Paediatric Anaesthetic Group provides flexible teamworking to deliver children’s anaesthesia in Oxford. This post has been designed to develop a collaborate link between the existing inpatient and outpatient pain services for children in Oxford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the interest of equal opportunities, we want to make sure that information about candidates is provided in the same format so all applicants should fill in the standard application form on the NHS Jobs website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
